00:38:45.850 --> 00:38:50.590
which is the strength of our
country is in our teachers.

00:38:50.590 --> 00:38:52.510
And --

00:38:52.510 --> 00:39:02.190
[ Applause ]

00:39:02.190 --> 00:39:08.220
I, for one, really thank you,
from the bottom of my heart,

00:39:08.220 --> 00:39:13.270
to every teacher whose
patience seems endless

00:39:13.270 --> 00:39:17.470
and whose sacrifice on all
our behalves is so great.

00:39:17.470 --> 00:39:20.000
You're never paid enough

00:39:20.000 --> 00:39:23.510
and you're never admired
enough, so thank you.

00:39:23.510 --> 00:39:32.230
[ Applause ]

00:39:32.230 --> 00:39:38.770
It took me a very very long time
to figure out that the best way

00:39:38.770 --> 00:39:43.770
for me to become less
discouraged was to talk

00:39:43.770 --> 00:39:46.810
to people about how I felt.

00:39:46.810 --> 00:39:52.960
You know, for a lot of my
life I would have self-doubt,

00:39:52.960 --> 00:39:56.670
I would be afraid,
I would be sort

00:39:56.670 --> 00:40:00.660
of anxiety ridden
about something.

00:40:00.660 --> 00:40:06.610
And I would try to power
through it and almost ignore it.

00:40:06.610 --> 00:40:10.630
And it really eats you up.

00:40:10.630 --> 00:40:14.710
It's like your stomach's
constantly churning.

00:40:14.710 --> 00:40:19.410
And in the end, when
you're discouraged,

00:40:19.410 --> 00:40:22.380
you can't find the
good in things,

00:40:22.380 --> 00:40:24.830
because you're discouraged.

00:40:24.830 --> 00:40:29.540
And, so, it took me a long
time to realize I have

00:40:29.540 --> 00:40:33.580
to share what I'm
feeling with other people.

00:40:33.580 --> 00:40:38.310
Now, that's not so easy,
because sometimes you look

00:40:38.310 --> 00:40:42.300
at your parents and they may
be unhappy about something

00:40:42.300 --> 00:40:46.050
and you don't want to make
them more unhappy, right?

00:40:46.050 --> 00:40:48.020
So, maybe they're
not the best person

00:40:48.020 --> 00:40:50.980
to share it with at that moment.

00:40:50.980 --> 00:40:54.670
Although I learned and it
took me a long, long, long,

00:40:54.670 --> 00:41:00.370
long time in my life that when
I share things with my mom,

00:41:00.370 --> 00:41:04.280
she made such a big
difference in helping me deal

00:41:04.280 --> 00:41:06.350
with what I was dealing.

00:41:06.350 --> 00:41:11.860
But, if that doesn't
or can't work for you,

00:41:11.860 --> 00:41:15.350
there's always a teacher.

00:41:15.350 --> 00:41:18.880
Sometimes there's the
parent of a neighbor or one

00:41:18.880 --> 00:41:25.380
of your best friends, sometimes
it's someone in your Sunday

00:41:25.380 --> 00:41:29.290
or Saturday school
religious experience.

00:41:29.290 --> 00:41:32.920
And sometimes it's
just another friend.

00:41:32.920 --> 00:41:35.720
And if you're a good
friend and somebody comes

00:41:35.720 --> 00:41:39.130
to you who's a friend and
says, "I'm in trouble,

00:41:39.130 --> 00:41:42.800
you have to help them find
an adult to help you."

00:41:42.800 --> 00:41:46.490
That's what being a good
friend is when you're little.

00:41:46.490 --> 00:41:52.330
But, in the end, I think it's
important for every child

00:41:52.330 --> 00:41:56.310
to know that they're not alone.

00:41:56.310 --> 00:42:00.580
That what they feel are things
that other children have felt,

00:42:00.580 --> 00:42:05.230
even children like
me when I was little.

00:42:05.230 --> 00:42:09.550
And, so, to me, that's
the first lesson.

00:42:09.550 --> 00:42:13.130
Learn how to share
what's bothering you.

00:42:13.130 --> 00:42:14.430
Good luck to you.

