or may be doing things
in a different way,

00:44:57.660 --> 00:45:05.200
that they're not strange,
they're just like you and me

00:45:05.200 --> 00:45:09.860
and they have a condition that
they have to take medicine for

00:45:09.860 --> 00:45:14.020
or accommodate for,
but they're just

00:45:14.020 --> 00:45:17.220
as important as anybody else.

00:45:17.220 --> 00:45:22.360
And that difference
enriches our lives.

00:45:22.360 --> 00:45:26.890
So, I have kids who are blind
and I have kids in wheelchairs,

00:45:26.890 --> 00:45:30.750
I have kids with attention
deficit and Tourette syndrome

00:45:30.750 --> 00:45:35.070
and downs syndrome, and
each of them has a vignette

00:45:35.070 --> 00:45:39.220
where they describe their
condition and they describe how

00:45:39.220 --> 00:45:41.260
that condition has
made them stronger.

00:45:41.260 --> 00:45:48.760
And it's set in a garden, and
in that garden scene I point

00:45:48.760 --> 00:45:56.870
out to kids, some trees
need shade, some need life.

00:45:56.870 --> 00:46:04.820
Some plants need water, and
some plants need very little.

00:46:04.820 --> 00:46:08.390
And yet together
all of those plants

00:46:08.390 --> 00:46:12.250
and trees create a
beautiful garden.

00:46:12.250 --> 00:46:17.110
And together all of us who are
different create a better world.

00:46:17.110 --> 00:46:18.410
Thank you.

00:46:18.410 --> 00:46:24.130
Thank you for asking
your question.

00:46:24.130 --> 00:46:25.430
&gt;&gt; You're doing such good work.

00:46:25.430 --> 00:46:27.230
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA
SOTOMAYOR: Thank you.

00:46:27.230 --> 00:46:35.170
[ Applause ]

00:46:35.170 --> 00:46:36.470
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN:
And, Justice, the --

00:46:36.470 --> 00:46:37.770
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:
they promise you a picture.

00:46:37.770 --> 00:46:39.070
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:46:39.070 --> 00:46:40.370
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA
SOTOMAYOR: Thank you.

00:46:40.370 --> 00:46:42.010
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: This was
the three part question.

00:46:42.010 --> 00:46:43.310
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA
SOTOMAYOR: Oh my gosh.

00:46:43.310 --> 00:46:45.770
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: With,
"You Rock," after each one.

00:46:45.770 --> 00:46:47.800
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA
SOTOMAYOR: Okay.

00:46:47.800 --> 00:46:51.190
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: How do you
maintain your hopeful outlook

00:46:51.190 --> 00:46:53.800
in these challenging times?

00:46:56.570 --> 00:46:57.870
You rock.

00:46:57.870 --> 00:47:00.610
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA
SOTOMAYOR: All right,

00:47:00.610 --> 00:47:04.850
who's this three part question?

00:47:04.850 --> 00:47:09.180
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: Who asked
that and wrote, "You rock."

00:47:09.180 --> 00:47:10.820
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:
Nobody's going to own up to it?

00:47:10.820 --> 00:47:12.850
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: They're still
there, this is three parts.

00:47:12.850 --> 00:47:14.640
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA
SOTOMAYOR: Oh, okay.

00:47:14.640 --> 00:47:22.220
We don't have a choice, do we?

00:47:24.260 --> 00:47:31.340
We don't. We have to
make the world better.

00:47:31.340 --> 00:47:34.440
I started by saying to
you, "We're not bystanders

00:47:34.440 --> 00:47:36.780
in life, we can't be."

00:47:36.780 --> 00:47:40.240
We can't let things
happen to us.

00:47:40.240 --> 00:47:43.560
Our responsibility is to
be make a better world.

00:47:43.560 --> 00:47:46.790
And when the time gets tough,

00:47:46.790 --> 00:47:50.390
that's when the tough
have to stand up.

00:47:50.390 --> 00:47:55.020
That's when we have to
get up and do something.

00:47:55.020 --> 00:47:59.770
And that's the whole mission of
my being a Supreme Court Justice

00:47:59.770 --> 00:48:03.930
and why I go speaking to
audiences all the time.

00:48:03.930 --> 00:48:07.210
I believe in civic
participation.

00:48:07.210 --> 00:48:17.410
And I believe that
that's a job not just

00:48:17.410 --> 00:48:20.700
for people interested
in politics.

00:48:20.700 --> 00:48:25.970
It's a job for every person
who wants to live in the kind

00:48:25.970 --> 00:48:30.170
of world that they think
is a fair and just world.

00:48:30.170 --> 00:48:37.340
And, so, for me when it gets
hard, I know I have a job to do.

00:48:37.340 --> 00:48:40.500
It's your job and my job.

00:48:40.500 --> 00:48:43.190
I can do mine this way,
because I'm a Justice

00:48:43.190 --> 00:48:45.640
and I can't get involved
in politics.

00:48:45.640 --> 00:48:48.120
But you can.

00:48:49.440 --> 00:48:51.510
So, get out there and make
a better world please.

00:48:51.510 --> 00:49:03.060
[ Applause ]

00:49:03.060 --> 00:49:06.970
Carla, I have to come up sit,
whenever like 10 minutes before,

00:49:06.970 --> 00:49:08.790
so you have to tell me.

00:49:08.790 --> 00:49:14.170
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: Well,
