00:49:27.800 --> 00:49:30.100
With a smiley face.

00:49:32.540 --> 00:49:36.830
Next generation of girls, Kelly.

00:49:36.830 --> 00:49:38.510
Where's Kelly.

00:49:38.510 --> 00:49:40.470
Oh, there's Kelly.

00:49:40.470 --> 00:49:45.570
Justice, could you go -- Kelly
could you go to the Justice.

00:49:45.570 --> 00:49:46.870
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA
SOTOMAYOR: Where's Kelly?

00:49:46.870 --> 00:49:48.170
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: Kelly's coming.

00:49:48.170 --> 00:49:49.470
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:
Kelly's coming, okay.

00:49:49.470 --> 00:49:50.770
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN:
Because another --

00:49:50.770 --> 00:49:52.070
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:
Hello, how are you?

00:49:52.070 --> 00:49:54.080
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: What advice
would you give to women

00:49:54.080 --> 00:49:57.440
who aspire to be
Supreme Court Justices?

00:49:57.440 --> 00:49:58.740
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:

00:49:58.740 --> 00:50:00.860
Don't ever let someone
tell you you can't do it.

00:50:00.860 --> 00:50:02.650
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: But
Kelly wanted to --

00:50:02.650 --> 00:50:03.950
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR: All
right, Kelly, where are you?

00:50:03.950 --> 00:50:05.820
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN:
Biggest piece of advice.'

00:50:05.820 --> 00:50:08.900
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:
We can become anything we want

00:50:08.900 --> 00:50:12.890
to through hard work,
getting yourself educated

00:50:12.890 --> 00:50:15.590
and as I said before, practice.

00:50:15.590 --> 00:50:20.150
But there's a lot of naysayers
who will pop up in your world.

00:50:20.150 --> 00:50:22.020
People who will tell you,

00:50:22.020 --> 00:50:24.650
"You're a woman,
you can't do that."

00:50:24.650 --> 00:50:28.390
Or you can't do that
because -- are you Latina?

00:50:28.390 --> 00:50:33.370
No. You look very
Mediterranean, you do.

00:50:33.370 --> 00:50:37.370
But they'll tell you you can't
do it because you're black.

00:50:37.370 --> 00:50:41.020
People told me I couldn't
do it because I'm Latina.

00:50:41.020 --> 00:50:43.570
You know, there was some writers
who said when I was nominated

00:50:43.570 --> 00:50:48.140
for the Supreme Court,
you're not smart enough.

00:50:48.140 --> 00:50:50.580
Those things hurt.

00:50:50.580 --> 00:50:53.710
When people show a lack
of confidence in you,

00:50:53.710 --> 00:50:59.370
it sometimes scares you away
from trying, but you can't.

00:50:59.370 --> 00:51:03.680
Because you know you and you
know how strong you can be,

00:51:03.680 --> 00:51:06.540
and you know how
hard you can work.

00:51:06.540 --> 00:51:09.460
And you just have to look at
people who say that to you

00:51:09.460 --> 00:51:11.900
and say, "That's what you think.

00:51:11.900 --> 00:51:13.320
It's not what I think."

00:51:13.320 --> 00:51:15.510
Good luck.

00:51:15.510 --> 00:51:21.500
[ Applause ]

00:51:21.500 --> 00:51:24.000
&gt;&gt; It's an honor to
be in your presence.

00:51:24.000 --> 00:51:25.680
I'm going to tell all my --

00:51:25.680 --> 00:51:26.980
I'm a teacher, I'm going
to tell all my girls.

00:51:26.980 --> 00:51:28.780
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA
