You're too far up, I'm sorry.

00:52:15.470 --> 00:52:18.900
Hi. Hello.

00:52:19.970 --> 00:52:22.070
Thank you, thank you.

00:52:22.070 --> 00:52:24.370
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: I'm
going to read the book.

00:52:26.130 --> 00:52:28.950
Because this is the
very last part.

00:52:28.950 --> 00:52:30.250
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA
SOTOMAYOR: All right,

00:52:30.250 --> 00:52:31.550
why don't you read
while I walk up.

00:52:31.550 --> 00:52:33.430
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: I'm
reading, because --

00:52:33.430 --> 00:52:36.350
and your beautiful illustration

00:52:36.350 --> 00:52:42.640
at the last is a puzzle
piece and it's gorgeous.

00:52:42.640 --> 00:52:48.040
And the words are, flame,
electricity, magic potion,

00:52:48.040 --> 00:52:56.570
friend, boat, snorkel, time
machine, launch pad, lens,

00:52:56.570 --> 00:53:03.470
teacher, life preserver,
mirror, map, key.

00:53:03.470 --> 00:53:07.460
The written word has been all
of these things to me and more

00:53:07.460 --> 00:53:10.680
for as long as I can remember.

00:53:10.680 --> 00:53:12.930
Like flagstones on a path,

00:53:12.930 --> 00:53:17.970
every book I ever read took me
the next step I needed to go

00:53:17.970 --> 00:53:20.420
and school and in life.

00:53:20.420 --> 00:53:25.330
Even if I didn't know exactly
where the trail would lead.

00:53:25.330 --> 00:53:31.330
Piece by piece the
puzzle came together.

00:53:31.330 --> 00:53:33.690
Where will your journey
lead you?

00:53:33.690 --> 00:53:38.230
And there's a timeline
of your life.

00:53:38.230 --> 00:53:43.590
And people can follow your
life through reading and books

00:53:43.590 --> 00:53:49.310
as they look at the wonderful,
wonderful illustrations.

00:53:49.310 --> 00:53:51.860
Now, I have to say that one

00:53:51.860 --> 00:53:56.370
of my favorite pages
was describing the fact

00:53:56.370 --> 00:53:59.120
that I was lucky
to have a library

00:53:59.120 --> 00:54:00.420
that was in my neighborhood.

00:54:00.420 --> 00:54:09.320
Walking distance from
the home, from my home.

00:54:09.320 --> 00:54:13.280
For hours I would sail
away to the wondrous lands

00:54:13.280 --> 00:54:16.960
and the stories I would
choose from the stacks.

00:54:16.960 --> 00:54:21.320
The library was my harbor
and books were little boats

00:54:21.320 --> 00:54:25.390
that helped me escape
the sadness at home.

00:54:25.390 --> 00:54:26.690
You can see --

00:54:26.690 --> 00:54:28.190
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:
Carla, could you hold

00:54:28.190 --> 00:54:31.020
up that page with
the little boat?

00:54:31.020 --> 00:54:32.320
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: The
one about the library?

00:54:32.320 --> 00:54:34.330
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:
The one about the library.

00:54:34.330 --> 00:54:35.630
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: Yes.

00:54:35.630 --> 00:54:36.930
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:

00:54:36.930 --> 00:54:39.910
My library card is
stuck in the boat.

00:54:39.910 --> 00:54:42.480
Lulu did research
and found an example

00:54:42.480 --> 00:54:45.250
with the library card
I had as a child.

00:54:45.250 --> 00:54:46.770
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: She
has a library card

00:54:46.770 --> 00:54:50.400
and it's interesting because
in this illustration --

00:54:50.400 --> 00:54:51.820
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:
And I assume every child

00:54:51.820 --> 00:54:54.410
in this room has a library card.

00:54:56.770 --> 00:55:02.960
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: In this
illustration the dark colors

00:55:02.960 --> 00:55:09.450
represent a time in your life
when you were 9 years old.

00:55:09.450 --> 00:55:17.480
And you felt sad and confused
and you needed to find a place

00:55:17.480 --> 00:55:19.850
where you could find comfort.

00:55:19.850 --> 00:55:24.250
And that was the library
and that was the harbor.

00:55:25.330 --> 00:55:27.880
&gt;&gt; JUSTICE SONIA SOTOMAYOR:
And that's still a place.

00:55:27.880 --> 00:55:32.540
Not just with quiet, but
with a sense of peace,

00:55:32.540 --> 00:55:39.510
because there you have the key I
found to life, the key of books.

00:55:39.510 --> 00:55:57.040
[ Applause ]

00:55:57.040 --> 00:56:00.640
&gt;&gt; CARLA HAYDEN: And for book
lovers everywhere, you said,

00:56:00.640 --> 00:56:03.420
"Books were my loyal
friends, they made it

00:56:03.420 --> 00:56:06.330
so I never felt lonely."

00:56:06.330 --> 00:56:13.700
And, Justice, thank you
for -- for everything.

00:56:13.700 --> 00:56:17.510
For sharing your
journey with us.

00:56:17.510 --> 00:56:58.040
